      ],
      "text": "Pyrrhus, after he became king, first\nattacked the Corcyraeans among all\nGreeks, seeing their island situated in\nfront of his own country and unwilling\nthat it should serve as a base of\noperations against him for others. After\nCorcyra was captured, regarding what\nhe suffered in the war against\nLysimachus, and how he expelled\nDemetrius and ruled Macedonia until\nhe was again driven out by\nLysimachus\u2014these greatest events of\nPyrrhus in that period, so far as they\ninvolve Lysimachus, I have already\nmade clear."
